Sirius Hires Manager Who Plans to Buy Oil Fields, Times Reports

-- B y   L i n d s a y   F o r t a d o
-- 
2011-07-31T09:25:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-31/sirius-hires-manager-who-plans-to-buy-oil-fields-times-reports.html
Sirius Petroleum Plc (SRSP)  hired a
commercial director who plans to buy Nigerian oil fields from
Exxon Mobil Corp. and  Royal Dutch Shell Plc (RDSA) , the Sunday Times
reported, without saying where it got the information.  Sirius hired Ed Johnson, formerly head of emerging-markets
oil at Renaissance Capital Ltd., to be its commercial director,
the newspaper said. Johnson, 33, may become chief executive
officer by the end of the year, according to the Sunday Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lindsay Fortado in London at 
 lfortado@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Anthony Aarons at   aaarons@bloomberg.net  